title: For Sale/Trade:  BEWARE OF THOSE TRYING TO BUY USED GUNS 4 RETAIL (NEW) PRICES
postcontent:
Quite obviously, if someone trying to buy a glock, or any other brand of handgun at the SAME PRICE for which they are purchased NEW, chances are they are not legally allowed to own one -- OR, they are so stupid/inexperienced that they probably shouldn't own a gun at in the first place.

My experience with numerable Armslist users dictates, that at least half of you do not give a single shit whether or not a person provides a NH drivers license or P/R License. Because you almost never ask it of ME during a trade or purchase. This has been my experience in over 12 face to face transactions conducted via Armslist.com.

Most of you, simply DO NOT care.

So if someone is offering to pay RETAIL PRICE for a USED firearm...guess what you should do?

ASK THEM TO PROVIDE A VALID NH DRIVERS LICENSE AND PISTOL/REVOLVER LICENSE OR YOU WILL LIKELY BE ARMING A FELON OR VIOLENT CRIMINAL.

Either that, or someone ignorant enough to buy a USED gun for that which it costs NEW -- and in such cases, arming a person who should not be armed in the first place.

Is it illegal to NOT ask someone to provide these things? Maybe so, maybe not. But what is illegal is selling a deadly weapon to someone who is not lawfully permitted to own one. And because you make that choice at your own discretion, you and you alone inherit the consequences of it. 

So THINK about who you sell your guns to, or the sweet $500 you gain now will be a sweet prison sentence later. 

You're welcome.

postcontent: Here is the cheap 20-gauge pump that you don't have to keep in the safe and you can actually hunt with. title: For Sale:  Concealed Weapons Permit Class (aka Concealed Carry Course) for $59
postcontent:
One of the requirements by the State of Florida to apply for a concealed weapons permit is to have successfully taken a concealed carry course under a certified instructor. Miami Shooters Club provides such a course with its team of NRA certified instructors - who will teach students the important fundamentals of how to safely use a semi-automatic pistol and revolver. Your concealed weapons permit will allow you to concealed carry in more than 30 states.

Miami Shooters Club's instructors carry multiple certifications under the NRA, have traveled abroad to train and receive firearm certifications, and are hand-to-hand self defense experts - having taught multiple seminars for the Miami Dade Police Department. Under their instruction in the concealed carry class, students will learn the mechanisms behind pistols and how they operate while learning how to grip the firearm, aim, pull the trigger, get into a proper stance, and much more. The class also covers many of the legal issues and expected ethics of concealed carry in Florida. The classes are designed for complete beginners who have never touched a gun before... but experienced shooters will learn something as well.

At the end of the classroom portion, students will safely discharge a pistol under the supervision of a certified instructor, as required by the State of Florida. Miami Shooters Club will provide a firearm, ammunition, eye protection, and ear protection at no extra cost.

Classes take place in Miami on Fridays at 6:30pm or on Saturdays at 1pm.
